

The death toll in the fire that raged through Guatemala's largest open-air market on Monday has risen to 18, according to reports reaching here.

The fire broke out in an area of illegal fireworks stands in the El Granero Market, set up temporarily near a section of the permanent market shops, fire department spokesman Ricardo Lemus was quoted as saying.

Witnesses said the fire was touched off by a burning cigarette, but officials said the cause of the blaze was still under investigation.

